title: For Sale:  SCAM ALERT - the saga continues.... a PSA for my fellow Armslisters...
location: I'm not really in Pennsylvania...., Pennsylvania, United States
postcontent:
This is a pretty pitiful story, and not only shows that I trusted in my fellow Armslister too much - but also just how vulnerable Armslist is to outside defrauders.  I would highly recommend that Armslist establish some kind of security/verification system like Gunbroker for personal identification....  

To begin - I've posted two different scam alerts yesterday regarding the two links below.... (ARMLIST NOTE: the posts are still up even though I've flagged them and let you know.  I would encourage any other Armslister to flag them as a scam....).  The only reason I reacted to the situation quickly was because some other Armslisters fllagged them as a scam, and I got an email (unfortunately right after I sent my money...).  I truly hope that no one else lost out like I have... 

Here are the posts that still are up, under a different email and account than last time...

http://www.armslist.com/posts/3351067/pennsylvania-optics-for-sale--nightforce-f1-mlr2-mil-with-rings-

http://www.armslist.com/posts/3351049/pennsylvania-optics-for-sale--nightforce-atacr--c445-moar

I filed a complaint with the FBI cyber crimes division, and have been working with paypal to get back my money.  Come to find out, the paypal email address the individual provided as his "wife's account," (which was a "verified" paypal account) - is actually a disabled woman who was being shanghai'd into using her paypal account as an embezzlement thoroughfare for a foreign national....  yeah... she fell for one of the "help me, I'm a nigerian stuck in the airport" emails.....  She has sent me the full dialogue of texts with the individual, emails, pictures, etc, and he basically preyed on a lonely, disabled woman - and used her paypal account as the pass-through for money via armslist listings... 

So the lesson in all of this?  If you're buying something from an individual online, it never goes without risk.  I would make sure if you're using Paypal to get the individual to send you an invoice for the good(s).  We all know Paypal is wonky about anything bang related, but there are abbreviated means for dealing with that.... 

Note:  I'm a 100% rated arfcom'er, ebayer, and am on gunbroker.  All of this is just meant as a PSA and a hope that some of us will ban together to not only keep an eye out for this individual, but others that might try this in the future.  

PS.  This scheme was so fixed, I emailed the guy and asked for the scope reticle, and model confirmation, and he sent me additional pictures that matched what he was trying to sell in the post.  It all lined up....  but I got jacked.... 

Don't get jacked....

title: For Sale:  SCAM ALERT - the saga continues.... a PSA for my fellow Armslisters...
location: I'm not really in Pennsylvania, Pennsylvania, United States
postcontent:
This is a pretty pitiful story, and not only shows that I trusted in my fellow Armslister too much - but also just how vulnerable Armslist is to outside defrauders. I would highly recommend that Armslist establish some kind of security/verification system like Gunbroker for personal identification.... 

To begin - I've posted two different scam alerts yesterday regarding the two links below.... (ARMLIST NOTE: the posts are still up even though I've flagged them and let you know. I would encourage any other Armslister to flag them as a scam....). The only reason I reacted to the situation quickly was because some other Armslisters fllagged them as a scam, and I got an email (unfortunately right after I sent my money...). I truly hope that no one else lost out like I have... 

Here are the posts that still are up, under a different email and account than last time...

http://www.armslist.com/posts/3351067/pennsylvania-optics-for-sale--nightforce-f1-mlr2-mil-with-rings-

http://www.armslist.com/posts/3351049/pennsylvania-optics-for-sale--nightforce-atacr--c445-moar

I filed a complaint with the FBI cyber crimes division, and have been working with paypal to get back my money. Come to find out, the paypal email address the individual provided as his "wife's account," (which was a "verified" paypal account) - is actually a disabled woman who was being shanghai'd into using her paypal account as an embezzlement thoroughfare for a foreign national.... yeah... she fell for one of the "help me, I'm a nigerian stuck in the airport" emails..... She has sent me the full dialogue of texts with the individual, emails, pictures, etc, and he basically preyed on a lonely, disabled woman - and used her paypal account as the pass-through for money via armslist listings... 

So the lesson in all of this? If you're buying something from an individual online, it never goes without risk. I would make sure if you're using Paypal to get the individual to send you an invoice for the good(s). We all know Paypal is wonky about anything bang related, but there are abbreviated means for dealing with that.... 

Note: I'm a 100% rated arfcom'er, ebayer, and am on gunbroker. All of this is just meant as a PSA and a hope that some of us will band together to not only keep an eye out for this individual, but others that might try this in the future. 

PS. This scheme was so fixed, I emailed the guy and asked for the scope reticle, and model confirmation, and he sent me additional pictures that matched what he was trying to sell in the post. It all lined up.... but I got jacked.... 

Don't get jacked....  if you have questions, you can reach me at:

REDACTED

title: For Sale:  Jamestown, NC LONG RIFLE FOR SALE
postcontent:
Hello,

Mom is looking to sell a rifle and thought you or someone you know might be interested.

This is a Jamestown, NC School rifle.  The Jamestown School, based in Guilford Co., NC, was famous for its long rifle makers.    The maker of Moms gun is Solomon H. (SH) Ward who was one of the last makers.

This long rifle is not as ornate as some of the Jamestown School.  Ward closed his shop was closed in 1902. He was quite prolific as only Anderson Lamb has more signed rifles that survive.  S.H. Ward was a large man and made few rifles himself, but had three workers that stocked rifles for him.  

According to C. Michael Briggs, an authority on NC Long rifles, most Jamestown Rifles made after 1840 were made as half-stocks with percussion locks.  The School did develop a few unique features.  90% of all Jamestown Rifles have a long, rounded on the end, three screw barrel tangs.  70% of the Jamestown Rifles that I have seen have a double brass dovetailed front site.  Most Jamestown Rifles will have a roman numeral stamped on the barrel (William Lamb and Anderson Lamb often used Arabic numbers on their barrels).  Each rifle would have come with a bullet mold with the same number stamped on the side flat.  I have five rifles that still have their original mold still with them.  One is even signed on the mold by the maker O. M. Dixon.  

Moms rifle is marked  X.  Sadly all the marking pics didnt turn out very well.

Moms is not an ornate rifle with lots of silver, but is in good condition.  It is missing its ramrod. It does not have the bullet mold.   It has been serviced and inspected by a smith who feels it is a quality gun.  Mom inherited this gun from her father, who lived in Eastern Tennessee and owned a general store and did a lot of trading.
